			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Is anyone Playing EQ2?<a name="74042"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 6 05 4:55 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I played eq2 for a while, and still do from time to time.
<br />
I played a shadowknight and a rogue.  Here are my findings:
<br />

<br />
1) scouts are by far one of the most fun classes to play.
<br />
2) I really like the way quests are done, but it would be nice if more of them were soloable.  Might take more time, but it would be nice to have the option.
<br />
3) there are still a lot of bugs, be patient if your gonna play it
<br />
4) It seems to be a lot easier to start off on the good side than they evil side.  I played 2 evil character and 1 good.  When my good character was around level 14, it had almost twice the cash of my level 27 SK.  ANd i didnt even do tradeskills on my 14 character.  The reason for this is the number of money quests that are easy, and repeatable.
<br />
5) Heroic opertunities are what seperate the good from bad players.  I've seen, ever after the game was out for a while, los of players who dont make use of them.  Granted, theycan be difficult to time correctly in a pick up group, but the rewards can be awesome ( free damage, free buffs, heals, etc ).
<br />
6) Their customer service still sucks.  I had several bugged quests, where i either couldnt finish the quest, or it just wouldnt move to the next step.  The CS reps would just tell me to /bug it and that there was nothing they could do. I find that hard to believe, since they have a tab in the petition form for &quot;quest related&quot; stuff.  They are still lazy and untrustworthy.
<br />

<br />
It is a fun game, but i think the thing that is holding it down is the seriousness of the atmosphere.  Games like WoW will always kick it's a$ simply because they have many different layers of enjoyment throughout the game.  Just because the game is in a medieval fantasy environment, doesnt mean you cant make pop culture jokes and puns.  If the EQ2 development team could lighten up a bit, get their customer service back on track, and fix bugs in a more timely manner, they might be on top again.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
