				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Is anyone Playing EQ2?<a name="74263"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 10 05 8:34 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've said this elsewhere, but I think that WoW is a great alternative to EQ2.
<br />

<br />
It's very stable.  It does have a small number of not-very-annoying -bugs.
<br />

<br />
It's ready for prime time, it's fun, has a slick interface, beautiful detailed world, works well even on lower end machines.  You can challenge yourself, or group as much as you want.   It has a nice PvP system, that is being expanded to be even better in the next patch.
<br />

<br />
It's a nice change from EQ.
<br />

<br />
I could go on and on, but I won't.  Try it out!
<br />
